WEBVTT

00:02.716 --> 00:04.415
Previously on Damages:

00:04.535 --> 00:06.735
SANCHEZ: I got some stuff
about how the military is

00:06.771 --> 00:08.470
handling soldiers with PTSD.

00:08.506 --> 00:10.706
I can get you interviews. I can
get you whatever you need.

00:10.741 --> 00:12.241
SIMON: If you do, then
McClarenTruth would love to

00:12.276 --> 00:14.176
help you present
this to the world.

00:14.211 --> 00:15.244
I lied about Torben.

00:15.279 --> 00:19.081
He is a very important financial
backer for this organization.

00:19.116 --> 00:21.216
McCLAREN: Why would someone
who provided Princefield with

00:21.252 --> 00:23.452
insider tips also
want to fund us?

00:23.487 --> 00:25.554
SIMON: I would never have made
this arrangement if I had

00:25.589 --> 00:27.790
known you were involved
in that crime.

00:27.825 --> 00:29.158
TORBEN: Soon it will be over.

00:29.193 --> 00:31.927
You'll get everything
that was promised to you.

00:31.963 --> 00:34.496
SIMON: Tell Mr. Herreshoff
I'm not pleased.

00:34.532 --> 00:36.966
You're saying your former
boss tried to kill you.

00:37.001 --> 00:38.867
PARSONS: I believe she
sent someone to do it.

00:38.903 --> 00:41.070
I think this is the blood
from the guy who attacked me.

00:41.105 --> 00:42.271
WILLIAMS: We got a DNA match.

00:42.306 --> 00:43.272
His name's Patrick Scully.

00:43.307 --> 00:45.074
It seems he left town
several years ago.

00:45.109 --> 00:46.875
PARSONS: So there's
no way to locate him?

00:46.911 --> 00:47.876
Who is this?

00:47.912 --> 00:49.812
STEFANIA: No, I don't know him.

00:49.847 --> 00:50.946
I never saw him before.

00:50.982 --> 00:54.049
PARSONS: If you think of anything
else, please give me a call.

00:54.085 --> 00:57.453
STEFANIA: I left Ellen
Parsons' card on the table.

00:57.488 --> 00:59.755
PATRICK: Thank you for this.

01:04.595 --> 01:07.266
PARSONS: The trial is scheduled
to start in a week...

01:09.652 --> 01:12.286
and you haven't
deposed my clients.

01:12.321 --> 01:14.488
HEWES: I'm aware of that.

01:14.523 --> 01:17.324
PARSONS: Well, you've had
plenty of time, so if you ask

01:17.360 --> 01:19.727
for an extension,
I'll fight you on it.

01:19.762 --> 01:23.697
HEWES: I don't
need an extension.

01:23.733 --> 01:27.935
I'm looking forward to
the trial beginning.

01:27.970 --> 01:30.804
I'll depose your
clients this week.

01:30.840 --> 01:35.109
PARSONS: How many days?

01:35.144 --> 01:36.377
HEWES: One.

01:36.412 --> 01:39.246
PARSONS: To depose three people?

01:39.282 --> 01:45.319
HEWES: One day should
be sufficient.

01:45.354 --> 01:48.789
PARSONS: One it is.

01:48.824 --> 01:54.662
HEWES: I see you're making
quite a splash in the news.

01:54.697 --> 01:59.099
I understand some very big
clients may be coming your way.

01:59.135 --> 02:00.301
PARSONS: Yes.

02:00.336 --> 02:04.571
HEWES: Be careful, Ellen.

02:04.607 --> 02:09.443
A taste of success
can be tricky.

02:09.478 --> 02:11.312
PARSONS: Why is that?

02:11.347 --> 02:18.552
HEWES: It makes failure
that much more... painful.

02:21.623 --> 02:25.859
PARSONS: Thanks for the advice.

02:25.895 --> 02:29.330
(door opens)

02:34.970 --> 02:38.372
(elevator bell dings)

02:40.000 --> 02:46.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:52.253 --> 02:54.822
(pigeon coos)

03:39.934 --> 03:41.969
(pigeon cooing)

03:45.907 --> 03:48.809
♪ Little lamb ♪

03:59.888 --> 04:06.727
♪ When I am through with you
There won't be anything left

04:06.762 --> 04:13.467
♪ When I am through with you
There won't be anything left

04:13.502 --> 04:17.538
When I am through with you. ♪

04:23.578 --> 04:26.822
HERRESHOFF: We're looking forward
to sharing our strategy with you.

04:27.950 --> 04:30.651
Covered derivatives, long spread
commodities-- it's all old news.

04:30.686 --> 04:33.454
We don't want to compete on a
field littered with corpses.

04:33.489 --> 04:37.624
NAOMI: The whole idea of Fund 23
is to carve out virgin territory.

04:37.660 --> 04:40.561
MAN: Find the 14-year-old
girl who will become

04:40.596 --> 04:41.562
the next supermodel, no?

04:41.597 --> 04:44.298
HERRESHOFF: Molto buono.

04:44.333 --> 04:45.833
MAN: Well, I like
what I've heard.

04:45.868 --> 04:47.835
NAOMI: Thank you for
the private showing.

04:47.870 --> 04:49.169
Beautiful works.

04:49.205 --> 04:50.170
Just really beautiful.

04:50.206 --> 04:51.672
MAN: It was my pleasure, really.

04:51.707 --> 04:53.707
So we'll pick up your team
tomorrow morning at your hotel

04:53.742 --> 04:55.642
and we'll go over
the details, okay?

04:55.678 --> 04:57.311
HERRESHOFF: Excellent.
Ciao.

04:57.346 --> 04:58.312
MAN: Ciao, arrivederci.

04:58.347 --> 04:59.246
NAOMI: Grazie.

04:59.281 --> 05:00.981
(speaks Italian)

05:01.016 --> 05:02.850
NAOMI: That went well.

05:02.885 --> 05:04.852
HERRESHOFF: Cocksucker's
on the hook.

05:04.887 --> 05:08.622
If you and Bruce can't reel him
in tomorrow, you're fired.

05:08.657 --> 05:09.923
So, uh, late lunch?

05:09.959 --> 05:14.061
Someone told me about this little
ristorante on the Via Soldati.

05:14.096 --> 05:16.997
NAOMI: Thanks, I'm going to head back to the hotel.
I'm still fighting this jet lag.

05:17.032 --> 05:19.733
HERRESHOFF: Well, what
are you doing later?

05:19.768 --> 05:21.935
NAOMI: Bennett, I told you.

05:21.971 --> 05:23.570
HERRESHOFF: Come on.

05:23.606 --> 05:26.607
We're in Rome.

05:26.642 --> 05:27.608
(ringtone playing)

05:27.643 --> 05:28.842
One last time.

05:28.878 --> 05:32.513
Let's go out in style.

05:32.548 --> 05:34.715
NAOMI: I got to go.

05:34.750 --> 05:37.251
I'll see you tomorrow.

05:42.524 --> 05:47.961
Well, that wasn't how I
thought this was going to go.

05:47.997 --> 05:51.565
This your standard procedure?

05:51.600 --> 05:54.902
You don't do this with everyone
who offers you information.

05:54.937 --> 05:58.705
McCLAREN: No, of course not.

05:58.741 --> 06:01.575
NAOMI: What do you think?

06:01.610 --> 06:04.011
McCLAREN: It was nice.

06:04.046 --> 06:06.780
NAOMI: I mean Fund 23.

06:06.815 --> 06:09.483
If you see our internal
financials, there's a pattern

06:09.518 --> 06:11.785
that can only be explained
by insider trading.

06:11.820 --> 06:16.156
McCLAREN: Well, if I'm gonna help
you, I'll need more evidence.

06:16.192 --> 06:18.358
NAOMI: I can get you
all the documentation.

06:18.394 --> 06:19.359
(knocking)

06:19.395 --> 06:20.360
SIMON: Channing, you up?

06:20.396 --> 06:21.828
NAOMI: Jesus.
McCLAREN: No, it's okay.

06:21.864 --> 06:25.933
It's, uh, it's one of my people.

06:25.968 --> 06:26.934
What's going on?

06:26.969 --> 06:32.739
SIMON: Ready for your interview?

06:32.775 --> 06:33.874
Guess you forgot, huh?

06:33.909 --> 06:36.343
McCLAREN: No, no, no,
uh, I'll be ready.

06:36.378 --> 06:39.079
Just ten minutes.

06:46.984 --> 06:49.043
SIMON: If we could expose Princefield,

06:50.034 --> 06:52.437
that'd be a major coup for us.

06:55.764 --> 06:57.631
However, there is one problem.

06:57.666 --> 06:58.632
McCLAREN: What?

06:58.667 --> 07:01.001
SIMON: You fucked her, Channing.

07:01.036 --> 07:03.103
What in the name of
Christ were you thinking?

07:03.138 --> 07:04.871
McCLAREN: It won't be an issue.

07:04.907 --> 07:06.940
SIMON: How can you
be such a child?

07:06.976 --> 07:10.444
Do you have any idea how many ways
this could blow up in our face?

07:10.479 --> 07:11.912
McCLAREN: You don't
have to worry about it.

07:11.947 --> 07:15.315
SIMON: For the past eight years I've
had to worry about everything you do.

07:15.351 --> 07:17.951
Being your nanny has cost
me my wife, my daughter.

07:17.987 --> 07:19.953
McCLAREN: You're overreacting.

07:19.989 --> 07:24.024
SIMON: You don't get it, do you?

07:24.059 --> 07:29.296
Naomi Walling is a source at one of the
biggest investment banks in America.

07:29.331 --> 07:33.000
If you had any idea what it
takes to be a real journalist,

07:33.035 --> 07:35.235
you would understand how you
may just have compromised this

07:35.271 --> 07:36.737
entire fucking organization.

07:36.772 --> 07:38.171
McCLAREN: All right!

07:38.207 --> 07:39.172
What do you want from me?

07:39.208 --> 07:43.543
SIMON: I want you to stop
behaving like a fucking half-wit.

07:51.219 --> 07:53.186
McCLAREN: You okay?

07:53.222 --> 07:55.155
SIMON: Yeah, fine.

07:55.190 --> 07:56.156
Fine.

07:56.191 --> 07:59.426
McCLAREN: You want to be alone?

07:59.461 --> 08:00.927
SIMON: No.

08:00.963 --> 08:03.263
Come on. Join me.

08:11.172 --> 08:13.607
Give me one of those.

08:34.062 --> 08:37.230
McCLAREN: This leak
was a good one.

08:37.265 --> 08:38.698
SIMON: Yeah, it was fun, huh?

08:38.734 --> 08:42.068
McCLAREN: The way it used to be.

08:46.945 --> 08:49.363
SIMON: This business with Helmut Torben...

08:51.021 --> 08:53.160
I don't know how it happened.

08:54.483 --> 08:56.750
I vetted him, ran the same
background checks as always.

08:56.785 --> 08:59.786
He appeared totally legit.

09:03.124 --> 09:05.826
I'm sorry.

09:05.861 --> 09:07.694
McCLAREN: It's all right.

09:07.730 --> 09:11.898
I know you have my best
interests at heart.

09:28.383 --> 09:32.953
COOPER: Nice grouping, especially
for a concealed-carry piece.

09:32.988 --> 09:34.755
Chris teach you how to shoot?

09:34.790 --> 09:36.656
PARSONS: No.

09:36.692 --> 09:39.192
Another guy I used to know.

09:39.228 --> 09:41.661
COOPER: He taught you well.

09:41.697 --> 09:46.666
So... what can I do for you?

09:48.369 --> 09:50.337
Who is he?

09:50.372 --> 09:53.907
PARSONS: His name's
Patrick Scully.

09:53.942 --> 09:57.878
He did some time for burglary a few
years back and then he left the city.

09:57.913 --> 10:00.247
COOPER: And now you want
me to track him down.

10:00.282 --> 10:01.648
PARSONS: Yeah.

10:01.683 --> 10:03.850
That's his last known address.

10:03.886 --> 10:07.220
COOPER: What does this have
to do with the McClaren case?

10:07.256 --> 10:11.091
PARSONS: It's not
about the case.

10:11.126 --> 10:13.693
It's personal.

10:16.998 --> 10:23.036
COOPER: Look, I like this job,
but I need to know what it

10:23.071 --> 10:25.238
is I'm getting paid to do.

10:28.910 --> 10:33.113
PARSONS: A few years ago,
Scully tried to kill me.

10:33.148 --> 10:34.948
COOPER: Shit.

10:34.983 --> 10:38.151
PARSONS: And the police
investigation went nowhere.

10:38.187 --> 10:41.059
I was just able to get
this information recently.

10:41.692 --> 10:43.306
COOPER: Look... 

10:44.686 --> 10:49.268
I can't get involved
in some vigilante revenge thing.

10:51.033 --> 10:53.733
PARSONS: This guy is dangerous.

10:53.769 --> 10:59.973
I need to know where he
is and what he's doing.

11:10.017 --> 11:12.452
(beeping)

11:12.488 --> 11:15.522
(buzzer sounds)

11:30.238 --> 11:32.205
(click)

11:32.241 --> 11:35.275
(chirping)

11:39.247 --> 11:43.283
PARSONS: The importance of Mr. McClaren's
latest leak cannot be overstated.

11:43.318 --> 11:47.053
The U.S. military has routinely
subjected its own soldiers to

11:47.089 --> 11:48.588
psychological abuse.

11:48.624 --> 11:52.826
MAN: But there have been demonstrations
outside the Pentagon for three days straight.

11:52.861 --> 11:54.828
Does Channing McClaren take
responsibility for this?

11:54.863 --> 11:59.165
PARSONS: My client only takes
responsibility for telling the truth.

11:59.201 --> 12:02.402
These demonstrations simply
reflect the American public's

12:02.437 --> 12:04.037
outrage at learning the facts.

12:04.072 --> 12:08.642
MAN: Mr. McClaren is being sued by
Patty Hewes for wrongful death.

12:08.677 --> 12:11.144
How do you think this latest
leak will affect the lawsuit?

12:11.179 --> 12:14.014
PARSONS: I can't comment on
the specifics of the McClaren

12:14.049 --> 12:16.983
case, but I will say this.

12:17.019 --> 12:21.454
McClarenTruth is going to continue to
hold corrupt institutions responsible for

12:21.490 --> 12:22.455
their actions.

12:22.491 --> 12:25.091
My client is not going to be
intimidated by Patty Hewes'

12:25.127 --> 12:26.593
scurrilous accusations.

12:26.628 --> 12:27.594
(presses key)

12:27.629 --> 12:29.596
HERNDON: Legally
Brunette's on a tear.

12:29.631 --> 12:30.597
(Hewes laughs)

12:30.632 --> 12:34.467
I hear some major clients are
clamoring for her services.

12:34.503 --> 12:36.369
HEWES: Good.

12:36.405 --> 12:38.038
HERNDON: Good?

12:38.073 --> 12:40.941
What's good?

12:40.976 --> 12:43.209
What is this, the
"harder they fall" gag?

12:43.245 --> 12:46.479
HEWES: Is that the Torben file?

12:46.515 --> 12:48.381
HERNDON: Yeah.

12:48.417 --> 12:51.718
There's an article in there that
makes for very interesting reading.

12:51.753 --> 12:54.087
HEWES: Anything I can work
with for the deposition?

12:54.122 --> 12:58.158
HERNDON: See for yourself.

13:03.764 --> 13:09.869
PARSONS: What's it been like at the V.A.
since the leak was posted?

13:09.905 --> 13:13.306
SANCHEZ: It's strange to hear
everyone wondering who did it,

13:13.342 --> 13:17.911
but... all the vets are glad
the information went public.

13:17.946 --> 13:20.914
PARSONS: That must
make you feel good.

13:20.949 --> 13:22.882
SANCHEZ: Yeah, it does.

13:22.918 --> 13:25.619
Seems like it was
okay for you, too.

13:25.654 --> 13:28.421
I keep reading your quotes
in all the articles.

13:28.457 --> 13:33.193
PARSONS: I feel guilty I've
been getting so much attention.

13:33.228 --> 13:39.499
You're the one who
took the risk.

13:39.534 --> 13:40.500
SANCHEZ: Wait a minute.

13:40.535 --> 13:42.636
Where you going?

13:42.671 --> 13:45.939
PARSONS: I've got to get some
work done on the deposition.

13:45.974 --> 13:50.477
SANCHEZ: No, you don't.

13:50.512 --> 13:52.779
(phone ringing)

13:52.814 --> 13:56.316
PARSONS: Shit.

13:56.351 --> 13:58.818
Sorry.

13:58.854 --> 14:01.888
One sec.

14:04.425 --> 14:06.893
Hey, Mom.

14:06.928 --> 14:09.562
Okay, just calm down.

14:09.598 --> 14:12.632
Tell me what's going on.

14:15.703 --> 14:17.904
DENISE: He keeps calling.

14:17.939 --> 14:20.206
Every night.

14:20.275 --> 14:24.944
Lecturing me, telling me how
stupid I am for leaving.

14:24.980 --> 14:27.614
Telling me I've
shamed the family.

14:27.649 --> 14:30.016
PARSONS: Shamed the family?

14:30.052 --> 14:35.388
DENISE: He says I've humiliated him, and
he's embarrassed to be seen at work,

14:35.424 --> 14:36.790
at church.

14:36.825 --> 14:37.924
SANCHEZ: Here you go.

14:37.959 --> 14:39.125
DENISE: Thank you, Chris.

14:39.161 --> 14:40.493
SANCHEZ: Sure.

14:40.529 --> 14:41.761
I'm gonna take a walk, okay?

14:41.797 --> 14:42.762
PARSONS: Okay.

14:42.798 --> 14:43.763
SANCHEZ: All right.

14:43.799 --> 14:48.068
DENISE: Bye.

14:48.103 --> 14:52.439
PARSONS: What happened tonight?

14:52.474 --> 14:56.176
DENISE: He came to the new
apartment, furious, pounding on

14:56.211 --> 15:01.147
the door, screaming
for me to come home.

15:01.183 --> 15:02.615
I was terrified.

15:03.382 --> 15:06.167
Thought he was gonna
smash the door in.

15:06.522 --> 15:08.623
PARSONS: What did you do?

15:09.725 --> 15:11.289
DENISE: I pretended
I wasn't home.

15:12.733 --> 15:15.331
But he...

15:15.914 --> 15:17.345
...sat 

15:18.101 --> 15:21.295
outside my door for two hours.

15:23.238 --> 15:26.372
I watched him through
the peephole.

15:26.408 --> 15:32.245
Finally... he left,
and I called you.

15:32.280 --> 15:33.480
PARSONS: I'm so sorry.

15:33.515 --> 15:35.849
DENISE: I can't go back
to that apartment alone.

15:35.884 --> 15:37.450
PARSONS: No, of course not.

15:37.486 --> 15:38.585
You're staying here tonight.

15:38.620 --> 15:43.189
DENISE: No, I can't keep bothering you.
I... (sighs)

15:43.225 --> 15:45.959
It'll be easier for everyone
if I just go back to him.

15:45.994 --> 15:50.930
PARSONS: Mom, you cannot
give in to him, okay?

15:50.966 --> 15:54.334
That's the whole problem.

15:54.369 --> 15:58.805
He doesn't respect you, and he never
will if you don't stand up to him.

15:58.840 --> 16:03.777
DENISE: How am I
supposed to do that?

16:10.885 --> 16:13.319
GARY: So... (laughs)

16:13.355 --> 16:15.722
This is Parsons &
Associates, huh?

16:15.757 --> 16:18.558
You even got a sign out front.

16:18.593 --> 16:20.026
Good for you, kid.

16:20.061 --> 16:21.194
PARSONS: Thanks.

16:21.229 --> 16:23.329
Why don't you sit, Dad?

16:23.365 --> 16:25.165
GARY: Sit?

16:25.200 --> 16:26.199
Uh-oh.

16:26.234 --> 16:29.602
Sounds like I'm gonna
get a lecture.

16:29.638 --> 16:32.472
PARSONS: I just want to talk.

16:32.507 --> 16:33.973
GARY: Yeah, sure.

16:34.009 --> 16:38.144
Let's talk.

16:38.180 --> 16:40.914
PARSONS: You have
to leave Mom alone.

16:40.949 --> 16:43.650
GARY: I'm sorry. What?

16:43.685 --> 16:46.052
PARSONS: She needs
time away from you.

16:46.087 --> 16:49.189
I know it's hard, but... GARY: No,
it's disrespectful is what it is.

16:49.224 --> 16:50.490
Walking out the way she did.

16:50.525 --> 16:52.892
PARSONS: Dad, I know this is
hard for you to understand...

16:52.928 --> 16:55.161
GARY: Hey, don't
talk down to me.

16:55.197 --> 16:58.698
PARSONS: I'm going to
say what I need to say.

16:58.733 --> 17:02.402
You've never respected Mom.

17:02.437 --> 17:04.704
I've seen you call her
"stupid," "moron," "idiot."

17:04.739 --> 17:06.973
GARY: 'Cause she acts
like a a moron sometimes.

17:07.008 --> 17:10.476
PARSONS: She's tired of all the
judgment, the constant criticism.

17:10.512 --> 17:15.515
No matter how hard she tries,
she can't do anything right.

17:15.550 --> 17:17.851
GARY: Did you talk
her into this?

17:17.886 --> 17:18.984
PARSONS: No, Dad.

17:19.020 --> 17:19.986
She came to me.

17:20.021 --> 17:20.987
(Gary scoffs)

17:21.021 --> 17:23.388
GARY: What does she think
she's gonna do without me?

17:23.425 --> 17:25.290
Support herself at a drugstore?

17:25.327 --> 17:27.292
PARSONS: What's wrong with that?

17:27.329 --> 17:28.560
GARY: Oh, give me a break.

17:28.597 --> 17:30.997
She doesn't want
to be on her own.

17:31.032 --> 17:32.131
She's throwing a tantrum.

17:32.167 --> 17:33.132
That's all.

17:33.168 --> 17:35.268
She wants attention,
just like your sister.

17:35.303 --> 17:38.538
PARSONS: You honestly think that
Mom is just looking for attention?

17:38.573 --> 17:39.672
GARY: Oh, you don't know.

17:39.708 --> 17:44.577
Your mother is very
difficult to live with.

17:44.613 --> 17:49.582
PARSONS: Dad... I love you, I do, but
you've got to be fucking kidding me.

17:49.618 --> 17:51.584
GARY: Don't you talk
to me that way.

17:51.620 --> 17:53.586
PARSONS: You're a
nightmare to live with.

17:53.622 --> 17:55.588
All she ever tried to do was
please you, make you happy, even

17:55.624 --> 17:57.590
when you were treating
her like shit.

17:57.626 --> 17:59.592
GARY: You watch
what you say to me.

17:59.628 --> 18:01.995
PARSONS: And it wasn't just
her; it was all of us.

18:02.030 --> 18:04.697
We were all scared we were gonna
get yelled at, humiliated.

